{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #143: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $A\\subset (1,\\infty)$ be a countably infinite set such that for all $x\\neq y\\in A$ and integers $k\\geq 1$ we have\\[ \\lvert kx -y\\rvert \\geq 1.\\]Does this imply that $A$ is sparse? In particular, does this imply that\\[\\sum_{x\\in A}\\frac{1}{x\\log x}<\\infty\\]or\\[\\sum_{\\substack{x <n\\\\ x\\in A}}\\frac{1}{x}=o(\\log n)?\\] Current best: Note that if $A$ is a set of integers then the condition implies that $A$ is a primitive set (that is, no element of $A$ is divisible by any other), for which the convergence of $\\sum_{n\\in A}\\frac{1}{n\\log n}$ was proved by Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er35}, and the upper bound\\[\\sum_{n<x}\\frac{1}{n}\\ll \\frac{\\log x}{\\sqrt{\\log\\log x}}\\]was proved by Behrend \\cite{Be35}. Prize: $500. Tags: primitive sets.","id":"vf_612543aa43fb5a8c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos143.erdos_143.parts.i https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos143.erdos_143.parts.i.","id":"vf_9c08775cc5facd50","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/143.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_612543aa43fb5a8c","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:143","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_9c08775cc5facd50","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:143","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted find